    "result": {"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"block":"learn-introductory-javascript-by-building-a-pyramid-generator","title":"Step 2","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>Your <code>character</code> variable currently does not have a value. You can assign a value using the <dfn>assignment</dfn> operator <code>=</code>. For example:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-js\">let hello = \"Hello\";\n</code></pre>\n<p>Assigning a value to a variable at the moment of its declaration is known as <dfn>initialization</dfn>.</p>\n<p>Initialize your <code>character</code> variable by assigning it the value <code>\"Hello\"</code> during its declaration.</p>\n</section>","id":"660eebd83100d37862268781","hasEditableBoundaries":true,"instructions":null,"notes":null,"challengeType":1,"helpCategory":"JavaScript","videoUrl":null,"superBlock":"javascript-algorithms-and-data-structures-v8","translationPending":false,"forumTopicId":null,"fields":{"blockName":"learn-introductory-javascript-by-building-a-pyramid-generator","slug":"/learn/javascript-algorithms-and-data-structures-v8/learn-introductory-javascript-by-building-a-pyramid-generator/step-2","tests":[{"text":"<p>You should use the assignment operator <code>=</code>.</p>","testString":"assert.match(code, /let\\s+character\\s*=/);"},{"text":"<p>You should use the string <code>\"Hello\"</code>.</p>","testString":"assert.match(code, /('|\")Hello\\1/);"},{"text":"<p>You should use double quotes for your <code>\"Hello\"</code> string.</p>","testString":"assert.match(code, /\"Hello\"/);"},{"text":"<p>You should assign <code>\"Hello\"</code> to your <code>character</code> variable.</p>","testString":"assert.equal(character, \"Hello\");"}]},"required":[],"usesMultifileEditor":true,"challengeFiles":[{"fileKey":"scriptjs","ext":"js","name":"script","contents":"let character;","head":"","tail":"","editableRegionBoundaries":[0,2],"history":["script.js"]}]}}},"pageContext":{"challengeMeta":{"blockHashSlug":"/learn/javascript-al